        "discriminators": [
          "Black-powder discharge: a subsonic ball means NO supersonic ballistic crack, so the high band is weaker and the spectral centroid lower than a modern RIFLE, and the report is duller and slightly slower-rising.",
          "Not separable from GUNS-PISTOL / GUNS-RIFLE / GUNS-SHOTGUN by morphology — all four are a loud impulsive transient with an LF thump, an HF crack and a reverb tail. The HF deficit and the long smoky tail are the only leans and both are weak. Commit only with text agreement.",
          "Longer and lower-centroid than GUNS-SUPPRESSED, which has a truncated tail."
        ],
