        "discriminators": [
          "The one genuinely measurable gun-SIZE cue: far more sub-200 Hz energy and a much longer duration and decay tail than any small arm. A howitzer is a multi-second low-frequency event; a rifle is a few hundred milliseconds. Weak but real — narrowable, not separable.",
          "Against GUNS-CANNON: modern smokeless artillery is sharper and slightly brighter than a black-powder CANNON, whose tail is longer and more smeared. Do not commit on that boundary from signal alone; it is a period distinction, not an acoustic one.",
          "Against EXPLOSIONS-REAL: acoustically the same event. A gun report IS a detonation. Text must decide."
        ],
