        "discriminators": [
          "RATE OF FIRE is the discriminator and it is unambiguous. Automatic fire is a PERIODIC IMPULSE TRAIN: roughly 8-15 onsets per second (480-900 rpm) with HIGH onset_periodicity. Nothing else in GUNS is rhythmic. Energy is spread across the file (envelope_temporal_centroid near the middle) rather than front-loaded as in a one-shot.",
          "Against FIREWORKS-RECREATIONAL, the other dense onset train in this taxonomy: firecrackers are STOCHASTIC (onset_periodicity ~0.2, a ragged burning fuse); a machine gun is PERIODIC (~0.75, a machine). That single feature carries the boundary.",
          "Against GUNS-RIFLE / GUNS-PISTOL: transient_count and onset_rate_per_second. A one-shot has neither a train nor a period.",
          "Stated honestly: the subcategory also admits auto-CAPABLE weapons fired singly, and such a file is morphologically identical to GUNS-RIFLE. The rate priors then contribute nothing and text must decide. The rhythmic case is separable; the single-shot case is not."
        ],
        "confusable_with": [
          "GUNRif",
          "GUNPis",
          "FRWKRec",
