        "discriminators": [
          "FOLEY-class, not gunshot-class. Route by LOUDNESS and morphology BEFORE attempting source identification: a handling gesture is quiet (low root_mean_square_level, LUFS well below -12), carries no LF blast and excites no room tail. The loudness gates alone rule out every firing subcategory, and that is a big, cheap win.",
          "Against GUNS-MECHANISM: HANDLE is the hand and the holster — grabs, holstering, dropping, catching — so it carries leather/cloth friction and a longer, softer, multi-part envelope. MECHANISM is a bare metallic click with a faster attack and a higher crest factor. The two overlap heavily; narrowable at best.",
